03:23.003 --> 03:28.250
It's up in the $4,000, and I don't care to pay that much.

03:28.290 --> 03:29.131
So there are limits.

03:29.592 --> 03:35.559
Oh, yeah, depending on the importance and where it fits in.

03:35.579 --> 03:36.961
Like an important piece.

03:37.983 --> 03:47.475
See, I got, here's this sub, sub collection.

03:49.143 --> 03:56.994
And Byrne-Jones intended to do an illustrated version of the Cupid and Psyche story from Apuleius.

03:59.137 --> 04:11.554
And Morris, Byrne-Jones did designs, and they were cut in the wood blocks.

04:11.675 --> 04:14.999
Morris did mostly engraving himself, which is from now.

04:15.901 --> 04:19.065
And they went to the best printer in London at the time.

04:19.670 --> 04:28.962
and tried the text, and it was so limp compared to the guts of the woodblocks, they said, no way, and they abandoned it.

04:30.865 --> 04:46.926
Only after Morris had designed the Troy type did they actually set up some, I think, five pages at the Kelmscott Press using

04:53.302 --> 05:19.782
So after they had the Troy type, then you had, let's say, they would both sit on the page happily together.

05:20.588 --> 05:42.791
Now, from those five pages that were set up at the Kelmscott Press, this rampant Lyons press in London got permission from the Cambridge University Press that has all the molds for Morris's Troy type.

05:43.552 --> 05:50.359
They cast enough type to print this, and they extrapolated from those five pages

05:50.643 --> 05:54.108
the whole book that Morris and Byrne Jones intended.

05:54.308 --> 05:55.570
That's nice, isn't it?

05:55.610 --> 05:55.751
Yeah.

05:55.771 --> 05:56.712
This is fabulous.

05:56.732 --> 05:58.294
And when was this done?

05:58.314 --> 06:01.499
This is on the... So it's fairly recent.

06:01.519 --> 06:06.987
Oh, yeah.

06:07.007 --> 06:07.708
Seventy-four.

06:08.209 --> 06:08.890
That's gorgeous.

06:09.631 --> 06:19.165
Now, before this got published, I had gotten a hold of, just like that,

06:20.208 --> 06:27.539
set of proofs, probably a unique set of proofs of the woodblocks.

06:27.559 --> 06:28.841
That's in this book.

06:28.881 --> 06:31.465
That's from Cupid and Psyche, PSYC.

06:32.447 --> 06:34.870
